      "id": "43cebd33ad46459e",
      "text": "[[Elena Esposito]]'s book \"Artificial Communication\" explores the concept of communication and its artificial forms. The book examines the ways in which communication can be simulated, automated, and synthesized, and the implications of these developments for society and individuals. The book provides an overview of the history and current state of artificial communication, as well as its future potential, and considers ethical and political questions related to its development and use. Overall, the book offers a comprehensive examination of the field of artificial communication, providing insights and perspectives that are valuable for researchers, practitioners, and anyone interested in this rapidly evolving field."
